This name (
brunneus
) refers to the concolorous dark brown appearance of the workers of this species.

caption.paragraph:
Figures 14-16.

Nesomyrmex brunneus

sp. n. holotype worker (CASENT0919844). Head in full-face view (
14
), dorsal view of the body (
15
), lateral view of the body (
16
).

subSubSection.paragraph:
This species occurs predominantly in rainforests of northern Madagascar from 25-800 m. The only southern population is reported from a rain forest of Isalo National Park (
Fig. 17
). The known samples are collected from canopy: canopy moss and leaf litter or rotten pockets of live branches.
